**item_#:** [[span class="name"]]NEED HELP[[/span]]

**object_class:** --Self-Contained-- --Keter-- --Explained-- --Euclid-- --Thaumiel-- --Safe-- --Inner Intestines Of A 4-Year Old Child-- --Apollyon-- --Neutralized-- --Aegis-- --Unknown-- {{[NULL]}} - SEE SYSTEM ADMIN

@<>>>@ log **special_containment_procedures**

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_1}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
All available methods for terminating [[span class="name"]]NEED HELP[[/span]] that invoke as much pain and suffering as possible are to be executed immediately, and with an audience of no less than --the entire world population.--
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_12}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
Any hesitation from Foundation personnel in entirely desecrating [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] will result in the restraint and live dissection of those responsible atop a makeshift cross crafted from Australian Buloke. They are to be left to starve and rot.

Constant reminders to [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] that it must suffer for eternity due to its crimes against humanity is necessary for the Foundations continued directives.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_37}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
Due to the inherent nature of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]], Foundation researchers interacting with the anomaly are to be continually scanned and observed for physical changes such as sudden inflation of heart, stomach, kidney, or genital regions, indeterminable facial features, and sudden developments of antimemetic properties concerning their --physicality-- entirety of being.

Foundation researchers caught sympathizing with [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] in any capacity are to be detained, maimed, and subsequently amputated of all digits. They are to be used as examples for any other personnel who attempt to pity the anomaly, and cannot understand the danger that [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] poses to all life within the universe.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_54}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
The assassination of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] has been deemed an absolute necessity for the continued existence of our universe and nearby star system //Alpha Centauri.//
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_78}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
The execution of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to be conducted at varying degrees, as these events are subject to change indefinitely with an increase of magnitude and effect as [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] --festers within all-- forever lives in the folds and bends of collective human guilt and desire.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_79}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] --is contained-- {{[SIGNIFICANT DATA ERROR]}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_93}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to be lured and captured immediately.

1 Foundation operative, masquerading as any popular female social media influencer under the age of 22, is to continually post online pictures until [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] establishes contact. Once [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] attempts communication, this Foundation operative must comply with the demands of the entity, until a physical meet-up can be arranged between the two. Once the two are acquainted online, this Foundation operative, disguised as their aforementioned identity and sufficiently monitored and protected by MTF agents, is to enter the residence of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] with the intent of capture. [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] must be captured before physical ██████ ███ ████.

Upon obtaining [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]], the entity is to be beaten indefinitely --until it suffers for eternity--. Following [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]'s containment, a memetic insertion agent is to be distributed throughout the world, which will entice those that it has affected that "a grand miracle" shall be held at [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]'s current location. Once the entire human population is forcibly shoved into its containment unit, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to be brought to its knees and branded with heated metal throughout its body.

It is to then be executed through extended medieval torture methods by --trained professionals-- volunteers. Foundation personnel are to continuously rip the individual limbs of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] from its body using specially crafted machinery reminiscent of traditional taffy pullers. Muscle tissue, fractured bones, and organ scraps ripped from the entity are to be frozen and immediately incinerated.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to be injected with CC43anL, an experimental material capable of lengthening the lifespan of any organism via rapid cellular regeneration and boosted immune cell count. This will allow [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] to survive despite its containment procedures.  

It must continue repeated containment procedures.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_96}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] cannot be contained through standard procedures.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
