{{iteration_115}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
Calls to [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] from Christina Chapell Adwater are to be redirected immediately. All money currently deposited within bank account 055567840, with a routing number of 63114289 is to be redirected back to their previous locations.

Upon containing [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]], it is to be injected with all available sensory nullifiers. It is to be left without the capability to smell, taste, touch, hear, or see. It is to enjoy every moment of this experience, following several dosages of concentrated dopamine. [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to --experience God--. This will additionally serve as a reminder for all Foundation interns that failure to establish financial security will result in the immediate destruction of all human consciousness.

Assassination is to be again attempted and --successful--.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_144}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is responsible for the murders of at least 15 people.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is be to chained to a 5m x 5m platform built in the center of Chicago, IL. With its mask removed from its face, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to be photographed and posted throughout the internet. Foundation researchers are hereby responsible for locating [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]'s victims and have them appear in front of the entity during its showing. Victims are to taunt and remind [[span class="name"]]HELP ME[[/span]] of every wrongdoing that it has caused beginning with Event 01, first documented on 2012/06/28. Failure to recite every Event correctly, and before nightfall will result in the immediate executions of all family members related to [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]. As traditional weaponry will not be brought into the showing area in which [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is being displayed, standard strangulation methods are to be used and enforced against the entity. Upon perishing from strangulation, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to be resuscitated and subsequently strangled again. This process is to repeat until [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] can fully comprehend and ascertain its sins against the people it has hurt.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] must continue living throughout this process, despite any pleas for help it may scream.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_169}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
Between the times of 10:00 and 11:30 A.M. PST of every Thursday, exorcisms are to be held at [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]'s childhood home to ensure that the entity suffers every moment of its existence here on Earth. This performance is to be held in the living room, with the corpses of its former colleagues Laura Rains, Addy Parker, Lucifer Droven, and an unborn fetus hung upside-down along the walls. All previous associates are to be found at [[span class="name"]]GODS DOMAIN[[/span]], a local church with previous allegations of workplace harassment. Failure of assuring [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] did not experience intense agony will result in the immediate termination of --all staff in Area-34--.

At 11:01 P.M. PST, Foundation operatives are tasked with beheading [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] and subsequently castrating the entity for the demons it has awoken.

The fears that it has let thrive.

The demons that share its face but cannot find their name.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_169}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
Complete degradation of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]'s humanity is no longer necessary. [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] displays no indications of previous humanity. [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] has no identity. All further attempts at perceiving [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] must be met with extreme caution.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_175}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] can be located within Area-34's Human Resources Ward. It is not permitted under any circumstances to counsel any more Foundation personnel, following allegations of violence and intimidation.

Upon containment of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]], All Foundation personnel are hereby approved to forcibly remove the entity's teeth directly from its mouth, preventing it from further speaking. Ordinary slip-joint pliers will be provided to all Foundation personnel operating within [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]'s containment. The proper usage of sedative agents has been heavily dissuaded.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_180}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
Every month [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to visit the gravestones of all currently deceased humans on Earth. It is to perform this act alone and without the aid of any Foundation members. Failure to perform this act within 24 hours will result in immediate cranial combustion and subsequent resuscitation. [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is to feel every ounce of pain that it inflicts onto others.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

