[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is Lola Adwater, a receptionist for the Foundation.

Upon discovering that her mother, Christina Chapell Adwater, was slowly succumbing to Alzheimer's disease and later dementia, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] realized that it could --help-- steal from her dying relative. After researching online, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] began to anonymously call her mother and tell her that she needed to provide funding for her grandchildren's education.

Christina Chapell Adwater has no living grandchildren.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] took every dollar it could from Christina Chapell Adwater. It did not feel any remorse or suffering from its exploitation. It later used this money to purchase a new house and car, which it used consistently without a second thought.

But [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] still craved more, and continued to wring Christina Chapell Adwater dry, until she no longer had anything to her name. Christina Chapell Adwater would later die, alone and with nothing to will to the rest of her family, all because of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]'s greed and desire.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_92}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is pleased by its abuse of --Christina Chapell Adwater-- an innocent mother who just wanted a peaceful life.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_95}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is --the Foundation--.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_115}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is former D-Class personnel D-19923, now --terminated-- festering in its cell, alive and healthy while its victims lay stranded several meters under drying soil.

The entity formerly known as Chad Mayers was responsible for the deaths of multiple individuals, all of whom were unable to discern his identity due to the mask that he wore as he --cannibalized their livers and digested their spleens in front of their families--. [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] was largely prevalent within Chicago, and was widely known for burning and massacring several families.

The cause for these murders is --unknown-- because it sought sexual pleasure and enjoyed seeing the desolation in the children's eyes as they watched their parents fall limp to the ground.

It did not feel empathy for the lives it has ruined. For the people that will forever be devastated by its crimes.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] must become afraid of death, and subsequently annihilated. Only then shall its sins --begin to heal--.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_124}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
The church named [[span class="name"]]THE HOLY KINGDOM[[/span]] houses [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]], formerly known as Chuck Gilmore.

Every Sunday, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] would perform large congregations for its community. [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] was largely regarded for its preaching and enthusiasm towards --God.-- [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] was considered to be the "perfect person," with a beautiful family and a nice house to die peacefully in.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] --didn't think so--.

Laura Rains, Addy Parker, and Lucifer Droven were associates of [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]]. They helped maintain the church and together everyone helped reform it into something that their community would be proud of. That they themselves could be happy with and bring their children to on Sunday mornings.

They did not deserve to be degraded, harassed, and beaten to death by [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]].
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_126}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
They do not know who robbed them of their lives.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_127}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] did --not-- know that she was pregnant with her only child.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_144}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is Johnathon Smith, former head of Human Resources, prior to succumbing to anomalous phenomenon.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] has helped hundreds of Foundation personnel learn to smile again. After being nominated for "HR Employee of the Month" for a second time, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] began to develop an abnormal obsession for white, pearly teeth.

How this occurred is irrelevant.

It loved --incisors-- --canines-- the jaws of those working under intense stress. It often fantasized about suckling the tooth pulps and nerve endings of those it worked with. The Foundation was unaware of his fascination. And, after so, so long, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] just couldn't take it anymore.

With a few words, [[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] was finally able to chomp and crunch on the enamel of its colleagues and acquaintances until they could no longer scream for help.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] wants --more teeth to snack on.--
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_150}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is none of the aforementioned individuals, but all of them equally.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_151}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
The entity is unaware of what it is and --wishes for immediate help--
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_154}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
No one is here.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_156}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is responsible for the collective 24.9 million victims currently being trafficked into modern-day slavery.

It is guilty of nearly 30 million cyberattacks yearly.

For the nearly 6,000 unsolved murder cases each year.

The $28.3 billion stolen each year.

--For all perceivable pain worldwide--.

[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is responsible for the extinction of humanity, claiming approximately 8 billion lives.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_156}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
...
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

[[table style="width: 100%; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 1.5em;"]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
{{iteration_166}}
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell style="border: 1px solid #f3f3f3; font-weight: normal; padding: 0.25em;"]]
[[span class="name"]]SCP-9615[[/span]] is the cause of their deaths.
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]
